  "content": "<p><strong>Tool:</strong> <a href=\"https://tools.simonwillison.net/qr-code-generator\">QR code generator</a></p>\n        <p>Claude helped me build this tool for creating QR codes, for both text/URLs and for connecting to WiFi networks.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Screenshot of a QR code generator web form. Heading &quot;QR code generator&quot; with subtitle &quot;Create a scannable code for a URL, text, or WiFi network.&quot; A segmented toggle shows &quot;URL / text&quot; and &quot;WiFi&quot; with WiFi selected. Below are fields: &quot;Network name (SSID)&quot; with placeholder &quot;My WiFi&quot;; &quot;Password&quot; with placeholder &quot;Password&quot; and a blue &quot;Show&quot; link; &quot;Security&quot; dropdown set to &quot;WPA / WPA2 / WPA3 (most common)&quot;; an unchecked &quot;Hidden&quot; checkbox; helper text &quot;Not sure? Leave it on WPA / WPA2 / WPA3 — that covers almost every home WiFi network.&quot; Below that: &quot;Style&quot; dropdown set to &quot;Square&quot;, an unchecked &quot;Border&quot; checkbox, &quot;Size&quot; dropdown set to &quot;Medium&quot;, and a &quot;Color&quot; swatch showing black. At the bottom is a blue &quot;Generate QR code&quot; button.\" src=\"https://static.simonwillison.net/static/2026/qr-code-generate.jpg\" /></p>\n    \n    \n        <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/vibe-coding\">vibe-coding</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/tools\">tools</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai\">ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llms\">llms</a></p>"
